15/02/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- President Boris Tadic vowed on Sunday (February 14th) that Serbia will continue its fight against organised crime, and urged other Balkan countries to do the same. After a ceremony in Pancevo to mark Army Day, Tadic called for regional co-operation against crime bosses. He added that efforts to fight corruption will continue as well. Regarding calls to hold early elections, Tadic said he expects the cabinet to complete its term, which expires in 2012. (Beta, RTS, B92, Tanjug - 14/02/10)
